data.name: reasonCode
data.description: The reason code to cancel the job:67 - Accidental opening creation, 51 - All positions filled, 49 - Filled by alternate source, 41 - Project was cancelled, 34 - No developer for requested skills
See the details of a Create a job opening
data.name: Create Job Opening
budget
data.description: The budget of the Job.Used for 'fixed-price' jobs only.

data.name: buyerTeamReference
data.description: Reference ID of the buyer team that is posting the job

data.name: description
data.value: A new interesting start-up requires an API ecosystem, ...

data.name: duration
data.description: The duration of job in hours. Used for 'hourly-jobs' only.

data.name: endDate
data.description: The end date of the Job. Only needed if job type is 'fixed-price'

data.name: jobType
data.description: Type of posted job.  Possible values are hourly and fixed-price

data.name: startDate
data.description: The start date of the Job. If start_date is not included the job will default to starting immediately.

data.name: visibility
data.description: The job's visibility. Possible values are: 'public' jobs are available to all users who search jobs, 'private' job is visible to employer only, 'odesk' jobs appear in search results only for oDesk users who are logged into the service,'invite-only' jobs do not appear and search and are used for jobs where the buyer wants to control the potential applicants

response.name: Category object

data.name: c1
data.description: Category name, for now the full list of categories

data.name: c2
data.description: Subcategory, which is related to category (c1)

data.name: dur
data.description: Engagement duration; Ongoing / More than 6 months = '26' 3 to 6 months = '13' 1 to 3 months = '4' Less than 1 month = '1' Less than 1 week = '0'

data.name: fb
data.description: Limit your search to buyers with at least a score of the number passed in this parameter.

data.name: page
data.description: Paging, based on offset;count, e.g. 0;10 - return 10 records, starting from 0

data.name: sort
data.description: Sorting, in format $field_name1;$field_name2;..$field_nameN;AD...A, where A eq. asc, D eq. desc, e.g. date_posted;A

data.name: st
data.description: Status for search; Open Jobs = 'Open' Jobs in Progress = 'In Progress' Completed Jobs = 'Completed' Canceled Jobs = 'Cancelled'

data.name: wl
data.description: Hours per week; As Needed < 10 Hours/Week = '0',  Part Time: 10-30 hrs/week = '20',  Full Time: 30+ hrs/week = '40'
